    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-29T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.00B/10–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-29T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 29, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:16 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3460. Information contained Deptel 2617, October 22,<note n="55"
                        xml:id="d172fn55">Not printed; it reported in regard to the Chinese
                        Communist bid for recognition and the Department’s position
                        (893.01/10–1949).</note> transmitted Director General, Political Affairs,
                    Foreign Office, who states Italian position similar to ours and that US would be
                    consulted by Italy prior to any decision on part of Italian Government re
                    recognition Communist regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
